b'HBNU Fogarty Global Health Training Program \xe2\x80\x93 2019/2020 Fellowship Year'
b'The Fogarty Global Health Training Program offers opportunities in global health research training for pre- and post-doctoral candidates from the U.S. and lower-middle-income countries (LMICs), sponsored by the Fogarty International Center (FIC) and several collaborating Institutes and Centers at the National Institutes of Health (NIH).\nThe program supports specific areas of interest in HIV/AIDS, non-communicable diseases, mental health, and maternal and child health and nutrition.'
b''
b''
b'Key Information'
b'Eligibility'
b'Apply Now!\nApply online at https://sites.sph.harvard.edu/global-health-research-partnership/'
b'https://sites.sph.harvard.edu/global-health-research-partnership/'
b'FOR MORE DETAILS\nVisit the link: HBNU Program Overview'
b'HBNU Program Overview'
b'Lauren Pedulla: lpedulla@hsph.harvard.edu\nPatricie Niyitegeka: pniyiteg@hsph.harvard.edu'
b'lpedulla@hsph.harvard.edu'
b'pniyiteg@hsph.harvard.edu'
